This solution uses a depth-first search (DFS) approach to check if the linked list is a subpath in the binary tree. The `dfs` function checks if the current segment of the linked list matches a downward path starting from the current node in the binary tree. The main function `isSubPath` then recursively checks the entire tree to see if any subtree matches the linked list.
